Operatives of Ogun State police command have arrested two suspected armed robbers, Osoba Yakubu and Ismail Hammed for allegedly snatching a motorcycle and killing the rider. Hammed  The Guardian learnt that on the report, the Divisional Police Officer of Sango Ota division, Saleh Dahiru, detailed police detectives to the scene, where the corpse was evacuated and handed over to the family, who insisted on burying him according to their religious belief. Determined to unravel the mystery behind the murder of the victim, the DPO and his men embarked on an investigation, and in conjunction with the community vigilante and So Safe Corps, Ismail Hammed was arrested with the motorcycle of the victim. Yakubu  MEANWHILE, the commissioner of police, Lanre Bankole has ordered the immediate transfer of the suspects to the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department  (SCID) for discreet investigation.